{
  "texts": [
    "Second, most of the clinical comparisons presented in this study are restricted to qualitative or semiquantitative analysis.",
    "There are many studies where multiple radiologist readers assess the diagnostic image quality blindly from the SR and comparison images to show the increase in performance [37,38,52,53].",
    "Ideally, at least five readers should be included from different levels of education and experience [54,55].",
    "We would argue that the ratings provided by the radiologists are also somewhat subjective, and the true ground-truth information cannot be obtained in clinical studies without a subsequent tissue sample extraction.",
    "Third, the weights of the individual loss functions were chosen manually during the early experiments of this study."
  ]
}